.SH "NAME"
Test2::Manual::Anatomy::API \- Internals documentation for the API.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This document covers some of the internals of Test2::API.
.SH "IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS"
.IX Header "IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS"
.SS "Test2::API"
.IX Subsection "Test2::API"
Test2::API provides a functional interface to any test2 global state. This
\&\s-1API\s0 should be preserved regardless of internal details of how and where the
global state is stored.
.PP
This module itself does not store any state (with a few minor exceptions) but
instead relies on Test2::API::Instance to store state. This module is really
intended to be the layer between the consumer and the implementation details.
Ideally the implementation details can change any way they like, and this
module can be updated to use the new details without breaking anything.
.SS "Test2::API::Instance"
.IX Subsection "Test2::API::Instance"
Test2::API::Instance is where the global state is actually managed. This is
an implementation detail, and should not be relied upon. It is entirely
possible that Test2::API::Instance could be removed completely, or changed
in incompatible ways. Really these details are free to change so long as
Test2::API is not broken.
.PP
Test2::API::Instance is fairly well documented, so no additionally
documentation is needed for this manual page.
